In the middle reaches, sections are navigable from Khartoum to Juba, from Nimule to Lake Albert, above which navigation is possible only in certain sections. Water transport is used not only by the Nile itself, but also by the Yusuf, Ibrahimiya, Mansuriya, Ismailiya channels, lakes Victoria, Kyoga, Albert , Tana [4]. The river is especially important for Egypt, where about 97% of the country's population lives in a coastal strip 10â€“15 km wide. The Nile periodically overflows in the lower reaches, flooding the entire valley. silt deposited during a spill.